Is there a risk that the sender will wait too long?
We hope that we will be a competition for large conglomerates just because we are able to deliver the matter the same day and for a fraction of the price.
At a large company for delivery within two hours, you will pay several thousand.
Here you pay a hundred or less, because that is the way someone already does.
Should traditional carriers be worried about the possible loss of customers in the future?
We hope it will be so.
The market has huge potential, huge multinational carriers feed here, as well as retail chains, where everyone started shopping and gradually found that the quality does not match what they pay for.
No one wants to find a note in the mailbox saying they have to pick up the shipment at the branch, first that day after 19 o'clock.
At that time, I had been in need of the package for six hours and I was waiting at home because it was important.
We want a better, faster and functional service that will not annoy anyone and sends a signal to the competition, let them try.
