How much money does a courier get after successful delivery of the shipment?
The courier determines the price and gets the full amount he asks for.
The sender is charged by a few percent extra for mediating contact.
This money is our profit, but it is only a few percent, because we want to push for volume.
Also, no one can charge the courier for not delivering the shipment when he actually delivered it, the takeover and delivery is verified using QR codes.
Are there any restrictions?
Whether in relation to the size or content of the package?
You can transport anything.
We've got three sizes, small as a cube of butter, medium as a plate of eggs and a big as a bass of beer.
After that, there is no further restriction and if someone has a seat in the car, he will transport the refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the app, so the courier can see what he wants.
You don’t even have to pack the thing if you don’t want to hide the content.
You stick the forgotten sweatshirt in the courier's hand and that's it.
Who came up with the idea and how long did it take to launch the service?
My friend got the idea more than two years ago, I didn’t pay much attention to it at that time.
