We are trying to respond to customer feedback and we are not so much addressing the foreign market at the moment.
We know it's a long-dalact run, but we don't rush, we want to create a really good product for people.
Shippanse LTD was the basic and most expensive application, the other two were in a way upgraded.
I will take it arose when we said that the national segment can be much more interesting and that we will at least learn it in the Czech Republic.
The third application Mesík is local, for the city.
But it can send the package to the exact address to the other side of the world.
It works for the sender as well as I take over, but the difference is that as a courier you see shipments in the form of points on the map that are closest to you, thanks to the geolocator on your mobile.
We called the application for couriers who want to make a living from this, we called Messík Profi.
So someone can make money by picking up packages around the city?
Exactly, the last application in Prague will be downloaded by a taxi driver, a student, a mother on parental leave, someone who wants to make the way to work.
As everyone is fooling around with those Pokémon now, they can collect exactly the same.
One sees where there are orders around the city, come to it, click and see when it has to be delivered and transports the shipment.
